verbose_text: We observed a significant increase in the mRNA expression of alpha chemokine CXCL10 (26 +/-6.51 versus 1.72 +/-0.30); TLR9 (11.14 +/-3.38 versus 1.46 +/-0.17), TLR3 (8.15 +/-0.83 versus 1.98 +/-0.41), TLR7 (5.71 +/-0.92 versus 1.80 +/-0.37), TLR4 (4.76 +/-0.88 versus 1.76 +/-0.38) and TLR1 (2.37 +/-0.33 versus 1.11 +/-0.10); and IL-23A (5.34 +/-1.14 versus 2.64 +/-0.53) in the liver of HIV infected versus uninfected mice.
